        "text": ", A.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Reprove",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἔλεγχε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐπιπλήξῃς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as in ver. 1 (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 18:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). There, the fault being a private one, the reproof is to be administered in private. But in the case of the sinning presbyter, which is that here intended, Timothy is to reprove the offender \"before all,\" that others also may fear, and may be deterred by their fear from committing a like offence. 1 Timothy 5:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Them that sin (τοὺς ἁμαρτάνοντας)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Referring to Elders, who, by reason of their public position (προεστῶτες), should receive public rebuke.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Rebuke (ἔλεγχε)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Comp. 2 Timothy 4:2; Titus 1:9, Titus 1:13; Titus 2:15. See on reproved, John 3:20.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Timothy 4:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Titus 1:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Titus 1:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Titus 2:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". See on reproved, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 3:20",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Others (οἱ λοιποὶ)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "More correctly, the rest. His fellow Elders.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "May fear (φόβον ἔχωσιν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "May have fear, which is stronger than A.V. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
